@startuml service_context_to_sgw_route_owner_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Service Context To SGW Route Owner Signal Flow\n(route/service context -> SGW security session and route-owner seams)

participant "NAV / vehicle /\nalert context" as ServiceCtx #F4F7FB
participant "SGW\ndiagnostic gateway owner" as SGW #E8F7E8
participant "Diag sysvar seams" as DiagSeams #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / tests" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Service Inputs ==

ServiceCtx -> SGW : routeActive\nguidedRouteActive\nspeedLimit\nvehicleSpeed\nalertLevel\nboundaryAlive\nwarningPathStatus\nfailSafeMode
SGW -> SGW : serviceContext = ethHasBoundaryServiceContext(routeActive, alertLevel)
SGW -> SGW : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(...)
SGW -> SGW : securitySession from serviceContext / diagStage / routeActive
SGW -> SGW : authState / securityFault / securityPolicy derived from diagStage
note right of SGW
Representative gating inputs
- routeActive / guidedRouteActive
- alertLevel
- boundaryAlive / warningPathStatus / failSafeMode
- speedLimit / vehicleSpeed
end note

== Route-owner Publish ==

SGW -> DiagSeams : Diag::SecurityState / RouteOwner
SGW -> DiagSeams : Diag::SessionState / GatewayOpen / TesterPresentActive
SGW -> DiagSeams : Diag::AuthState / SecurityFault / SecurityPolicy
note right of SGW
Representative outputs
- SecurityState
- RouteOwner
- SessionState
- GatewayOpen / SecurityPolicy
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

DiagSeams -> Obs : gateway security/readiness readback /\ntest evidence

note over ServiceCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Route and alert service context reach SGW
2. SGW derives diagnostic stage, session, and auth posture
3. SGW publishes route-owner and security seams
4. Tests and observers consume the effective gateway-access state
end note

@enduml
